c: 3
v: 75
t: "If you entrusted some People of the Book with a large sum, he would hand it back to you; while if you entrusted another with a gold coin, he would never hand it back to you unless you dunned him for it constantly. That is because they say: \"There is no way for such illiterates [to complain] against us.\" They tell a lie about God while they realize it"